---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Community">
  <main class="page">
    <section class="hero">
      <h1>Community</h1>
      <p class="subhead">
        A friendly place for machine knitters to ask questions, share progress, and learn from each other.
      </p>

      <div class="ctaRow">
        <!-- Update this href later when you decide where the forum lives -->
        <a class="btnPrimary"
          href="#"
          data-ms-modal="signup"
          data-ms-hide="member"
          data-ms-content="!members">
          Enter the Community
        </a>
        <a href="#" class="btnSecondary" id="contact-modal-trigger-community">
          Need to reach me directly?
        </a>
      </div>

      <p class="note">
        Just so expectations are clear: this is a member-to-member space. I’ll pop in when I can, but it isn’t the fastest
        way to get direct support from me.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="cards">
      <div class="card">
        <h2>What you’ll find there</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Questions and helpful answers from other knitters</li>
          <li>Ideas, works-in-progress, and “what would you do?” threads</li>
          <li>A place to keep the conversation going between videos and projects</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>Posting tips</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>If you’re stuck, include your machine, yarn, and what you’ve already tried</li>
          <li>A photo or short clip helps a lot</li>
          <li>One question per post keeps replies clear and useful</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>Kind & helpful wins</h2>
        <p>
          We’re all learning. If something goes sideways, it doesn’t mean you did anything “wrong.”
          Ask anyway—chances are someone has been right there too.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <style>
   .page {
  max-width: 980px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 8px 16px 56px; /* Layout supplies header clearance */
}

.hero {
  padding: 40px 28px;
  border-radius: 18px;
  background: #f3f6ef; /* soft olive tint */
  border: 1px solid rgba(82, 104, 45, 0.15);
  text-align: center; /* centers heading + text */
}

.hero h1 {
  margin: 0 0 12px;
}

.hero .subhead {
  margin: 0 auto 20px;
  max-width: 680px;
}

.ctaRow {
  display: flex;
  gap: 14px;
  justify-content: center; /* centers buttons */
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  margin: 18px 0 14px;
}

.note {
  max-width: 680px;
  margin: 12px auto 0;
}

    .subhead {
      margin: 0 0 16px;
      font-size: 18px;
      line-height: 1.5;
      opacity: 0.9;
    }

    .ctaRow {
      display: flex;
      gap: 12px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      margin: 14px 0 12px;
    }

    .btnPrimary,
    .btnSecondary {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      padding: 10px 14px;
      border-radius: 10px;
      text-decoration: none;
      font-weight: 600;
      border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);
    }

    .btnPrimary {
      background: #52682d;
      color: #fff;
      border-color: rgba(82, 104, 45, 0.35);
    }

    .btnSecondary {
      background: #fff;
      color: #1b1b1b;
    }

    .note {
  max-width: 680px;        /* keeps it readable */
  margin: 14px auto 0;     /* centers the block itself */
  font-size: 14px;
  line-height: 1.6;
  opacity: 0.8;
  text-align: center;      /* centers the text inside */
}

    .cards {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 14px;
      margin-top: 16px;
    }

    .card {
      background: #fff;
      border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
      border-radius: 14px;
      padding: 16px;
    }

    .card h2 {
      margin: 0 0 8px;
      font-size: 18px;
    }

    .card ul {
      margin: 0;
      padding-left: 18px;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .cards {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
      h1 {
        font-size: 32px;
      }
    }
  </style>
  <script>
    // Reuse the footer's modal behavior by delegating to the existing trigger.
    document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {
      const communityTrigger = document.getElementById("contact-modal-trigger-community");
      const footerTrigger = document.getElementById("contact-modal-trigger");
  
      if (!communityTrigger) return;
  
      communityTrigger.addEventListener("click", (e) => {
        e.preventDefault();
        // If the footer trigger exists on this page, "click" it to open the same modal.
        if (footerTrigger) footerTrigger.click();
      });
    });
  </script>
</Layout>